===Etymology===
{{ja-kanjitab|yomi=k|まぼろし}}

Probably from {{inh|ja|ojp|sort=まぼろし|-}}.  Used in ''{{w|The Tale of Genji}}'', completed in 1021.<ref name="KDJ">{{R:Kokugo Dai Jiten}}</ref><ref name="DJR">{{R:Daijirin}}</ref>

The initial ''ma'' is almost certainly {{m|ja|目|tr=ma, {{upright|modern}} me||eye}}.  The ''boroshi'' portion is of uncertain derivation, possibly related to modern [[colloquial]] adjective {{ja-r|ぼろい||rough, ragged, worn-out}}, verb {{ja-r|ばらす||to mess something up}}, or adjective {{ja-r|朧|おぼろ|[[hazy]], [[cloudy]]}}.

